<html> 
    <body> 
        <h2>Javascript Array Methods</h2> 
        <h2>Join() and pop()</h2>
        <p>Join() method is used to join all the elements of an array into a string. It takes an optional parameter which is the separator to be used between the elements. If no separator is provided, it defaults to a comma.</p>
        <p>Pop() method is used to remove the last element from an array and returns
that element. It modifies the original array.</p>
        </p> 
        <p id="my join"></p> 
        <p id="myfirstpop"></p>
        <p id="mysecondpop"></p>
        <script>
            var fruits = ["Banana", "Orange", "Apple", "Mango"]; 

            document.getElementById("my join").innerHTML = fruits.join(" * ");
            document.getElementById("myfirstpop").innerHTML = fruits.pop();
            document.getElementById("mysecondpop").innerHTML = fruits.pop();
        </script>   
    </body>
</html>
    